  "description": [
    "VOLUME IVNO 534 CHARLESTON S C TUESDAY MORNING MY 7 1867 PRICE FIVE CENTS TELEGRAPHIC Washington News WASHINGTON August 23_lt is said the ram Stonewall put into Norfolk in a sinking condition In crossing a flooded cieek near herc a stage upset and three ladies were drowned President Buchanan is recovering Stevens is reported as becoming alarmingly feeble The military authorities aro arming tho citizens in tho vicinity of Fort Sedgwick for the protection of the post Tho cholera is aging among the Seminoles Denver papers say Forts Keno and Kearney are besieged The cholera is reported malignant at Shawnee Town Illinois The Internal Revenue Roceipts today amount to 575000 A train on tho Annapolis Railroad wont itito a culvert killing tho engineer fireman and a boy Several passengers were injured and the train took fire The Turkish Ambassador was officially pre sented to the President today The Cabinet was in session from 12 to 2 oclock The pressure on the President for Cabinet changea is increasing Tho following is repre sented aa the conclusion of Sickles argument supporting his order Number 10 If the United States Courts in the re ba States be allowed to control the military authority"
